title: 1991–92 Division 1 (Senegal)
text:
The 1991-92 <a href="Senegal%20Premier%20League">Division 1</a> season was the 28th of the competition of the first-tier <a href="Association%20football">football</a> in <a href="Senegal">Senegal</a>. The tournament was organized by the <a href="Senegalese%20Football%20Federation">Senegalese Football Federation</a>. The season began in October 1991 and finished on 9 August 1992. ASEC Ndiambour won the first title and participated in the <a href="1993%20African%20Cup%20of%20Champions%20Clubs">1993 African Cup of Champions Clubs</a> the following year. <a href="US%20Gor%C3%A9e">US Gorée</a> participated in the 1993 CAF Cup, <a href="ASC%20Jeanne%20d%27Arc">ASC Jeanne d'Arc</a> in the 1993 CAF Winners' Cup and <a href="ASC%20Diaraf">ASC Diaraf</a> in the 1993 West African Cup.
<a href="SEIB%20Diourbel">SEIB Diourbel</a> was the defending team of the title. A total of 16 clubs participated in the competition. The season featured 450 matches and scored 301 goals. No new clubs came from the second division (Division 2).
Overview.
The league was contested by 14 teams with <a href="ASEC%20Ndiambour">ASEC Ndiambour</a> winning the championship.
